						<summary>

						<p>This is not dated and refers itself to the reign of the Bāṇa king <hi rend="bold">Mahāvali-Vāṇarasa.</hi> The king is stated to have ordered <hi rend="bold">Kendaḻiga-Perggaṅga</hi> and his son <hi rend="bold">Dēveya</hi> to repel the attack on <hi rend="bold">Pulināḍu</hi> by the army of the <hi rend="bold">Noḻamba.</hi> In the battle of <hi rend="bold">Miniki,</hi> Dēveya (?) is stated to have fought and died. <hi rend="bold">Bāṇavidyādhara</hi> <hi rend="italic">i.e.,</hi> the king granted Minuki to the hero's family.</p>						

						<p>First Face.</p>						

						</summary>
